-- Norges Bank Planning to Increase Italian Investments, Corriere Sera Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-11-08T07:49:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/norges-bank-planning-to-increase-italian-investments-corriere-sera-says.html
Norges Bank plans to increase its
investments in Italian companies, including toll-road operator
 Atlantia SpA , Corriere della Sera reported, citing  Yngve Slyngstad , chief executive officer of Norges Bank Investment
Management.  Norges Bank plans to make the investments this year and in
2011, the executive said, according to a weekly supplement to
the Italian newspaper. The fund is also interested in bank
stocks, Corriere said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  